      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SOLS ME NAME (3) is a lightly-raced but progressive colt who kicked off his campaign with back-to-back wins before finishing only 3.4m behind a Group performer when fourth at Melton last week. This looks easier and he should get his chance from this draw. LAMBRO MACH (6) did a fair job to be beaten just over 5m in a higher-graded race at Bendigo last week. Draws wide but has won at this circuit and distance before and his best form measures up. OLLIES THE BOSS (7) was first up for close to six months when he came from a similar draw to miss by just a neck as runner-up at Bendigo last week. Has won second-up before so can progress. MORRIS BROWN (2) has been producing some decent efforts from tough barriers of late including a second the last time he raced here last month. Draws for a good showing.",
